node.text:
Having grown up in Quebec, I can only imagine how hard this last year must have been for maple syrup producers, which is why I was thrilled to hear that @netflixca is supporting this beloved industry with a $10,000 donation to @macabanemaison. What’s your favourite way to enjoy maple syrup? 

Ayant grandi au Québec, je ne peux qu’imaginer à quel point la dernière année a dû être difficile pour les propriétaires de cabanes à sucre. C’est pourquoi je suis si enthousiaste de savoir que @netflixca va soutenir cette industrie que nous aimons tant en faisant un don de 10 000 $ à l'initiative @macabanemaison. Et vous, quelle place faites-vous au sirop d’érable dans votre vie?

node.text: Throwback to my Austin kitchen and the city that made this NY heat wave feel like a brisk fall day. TX brought me a lot of skills - paddle boarding, the ability to spot snakes underwater that were actually just sticks, but most importantly, snacking through the heat. It’s there that I got hooked on these refrigerated protein balls 🤤 featuring @ollynutrition collagen peptides. If you didn't know, my favorite gummy vitamin company also makes their own line of collagen. I love adding this flavor-less powder to my smoothies, coffee, and, yes, even these protein balls. Adding collagen to your diet is a great way to increase a natural occurring supplement that supports strong nails, hair, and bones 🦴 (helpful for my many, many paddle board falls) and Olly has 10 grams of it! #ollysponsored #proteinballs #hotasballs

Ahead of the long weekend, I’d like to introduce you to the iconic French classic croque madame’s cousin I totally made up and is in fact a sandwich and not a human but I anthropomorphize food it’s ok I’m fine I swear. It’s got mortadella w crisped edges, pepperoncini, melty provolone and damn it’s good: introducing the Croque Signore.

node.text:
Hi everyone 👋🏼. I’ve been thinking about this and about all of you a lot lately. Due to the ever changing situation with COVID-19, I have made the really, really hard decision to transition my book tour to a virtual format. This was the only way I could prevent organizing & encouraging large group gatherings that could have potentially put some of you at risk.  

I would have LOVED to celebrate the launch of Antoni: Let's Do Dinner with you all in person - this book has been such a labor of love I’ve put my heart into - but times are a bit different and despite wanting to see you all irl, I’ve decided to err on the side of caution at this time. If you've already purchased a tour ticket, thank you so much for your support! The ticketing venues will be in touch soon for next steps on refunds and virtual ticket transfers.

That said, I'm so freakin’ excited to share this book with you virtually. One day soon I hope we can all meet in person, but until then, I’ll see you all from my kitchen in just a few short weeks.

node.text: Today someone had the audacity to say that summer is "winding down" but I am not taking that on rn. Here is a summertime favorite: the burger. But not just any burger - this is my lamb burger with cilantro chutney. Inspired by the fried lamb patties I fell in love with at Asma Khan’s London restaurant Darjeeling Express, these have a tangy, cooling yogurt center that complements the richness of the meat. node.text: For your Meatless Monday consideration: Roasted Cabbage Steaks with Apple-Dijon Vinaigrette from #LetsDoDinner. Many of you have asked if there are vegetarian & vegan options in the book & the answer is: PLENTY. In this recipe, you'll find crisp, caramelized edges & a tender bite on the cabbage with tart, fruity notes from the vinagrette that bring a sweet brightness. The trick? Applesauce. Head to https://bit.ly/3rn5KGd to pre-order a signed edition from @barnesandnoble and get the recipe.
